customerNotes.note: Customer is still having issues with CloudManager. They are able to deploy successfully only in emergency mode.
There were some P1s over the weekend for the author (INC3124630) and three UJEEs (INC3124642)(INC3124641)(INC3124637). It looks like they are all related I will have to do an RCA for this incident

Customer has a pending large deployment. They have scheduled and cancelled this deployment four times. This big deployment is taking all of their focus and they won't entertain working on CloudManager or LTS until it's done. Currently the deployment has not been rescheduled

Craig is out this week. Chris Andrist is covering Honeywell for him. Peter asked me to reach out to Harsh to circle back on his dynamics ticket (E-002025534). I have not heard back from him yet. Elise invited me to the Tuesday (12:30 pm ct) meeting so I'll be sure to get an update at that time.

Brumoon Ahamat is working with FFB to implement CloudManager. As of last thursday (Jan 26) he estimates they will be ready to deploy to stage in another 2-3 weeks. I'll check back with him on progress weekly.
I pinged Scott Ryckman for a status on the FCC/ACS engagement
LTS upgrade to QA is at stage 5. I have invited the customer to deploy their code to the LTS servers and they are working internally to get that done.
They are still working on adding the provided LTS patches. They have a deployment on the 11th so her focus is there for the time being. She'll get back to this after the deployment.
They are changing the way they issue certs and have a requirement to automate the cert updates. I'll have to bring this up to the UHG team and get their thoughts.
Akhila will email Derek and Kirk and put me and Josh on cc. This is something that is happening UHG-wide so it's going to affect all UHG customers.
Got a response from Aravind and Scott. Aravind should have the SOW ready by EOD today

Customer got patched two weeks ago to ams-rh8x-aws-202512. The CDE said that he preferred that patch to ams-rh8x-aws-202601 because it was older and more established. I talked to the CDE and told him we need to patch monthly. Since this customer won't be patched to ams-rh8x-aws-202602 until March 4 (PRB0842560) I have reached out to the customer to see if we can patch them to 202601 tomorrow (2/4) or if we need to wait until the next patch window (2/18). I'll create a ticket for one of those dates based on the response from the customer.

Call with Harsh today. He had two issues to talk about. He's unsatisfied with Peter's response in E-002025534 as he says that this has been set up before with Mercer so he knows it can be done. I offered to set up a call with Peter to discuss further but he declined saying that there's no use if Peter will just give the same answer.

He also opened a ticket about their dev publisher E-002061812 that I'm working with Chris Andrist on. He's restoring from backup
Worked with Chris to get the dev login issue resolved

I got a response from Aravind. He has completed the SOW and will reach out to the customer to set up a meeting to review the proposed plan. I've asked him to invite me. I'll follow up tomorrow if he hasn't already responded.
Aravind sent out an email to Bruce and Cindy at Fidelity suggesting a few times for the call. Currently waiting on a response from them.
Created ticket for CDE to patch to 202601 during this morning's window. (PRB0842904) This was completed and the customer is now patched to the current baseline

Chase asked today if they have the ability to create a service account via basic auth to upload assets directly to production. After conferring with Mr Fluffyjaws I told him that could not be done due to security violations.
Customer is still working though some content issues with the large deployment. They'll meet next week to get those resolved and come back with a plan for this deployment.
Call is scheduled for 2/5 at 12pm

Akhila didn't send the email about the automated cert update initiative so I sent it today. I put Kirk, Derek and Josh on cc for visibility. I'll also bring it up on the UHG tech team call happening in 15 minutes.

Short manual deployment today. Nothing out of the ordinary and everything went smoothly until Chase tried to clear the CloudFlare cache. Seems they had an internal access issue with CloudFlare. He took that issue offline and said he'd reach out if there was anything more he needed from me.

I brought this up to Adi and the internal UHG team. Seems like this is an issue bigger than UHG because the industry standard is changing. Ed shared a link to the announcement about this change. We will need to address this AMS-wide.
Adi and Josh have a call with Kirk and Derek from UHG tomorrow. He's going to bring this up with them and see what their take is on it.
Meeting on 2/5 was with Bruce and not the call Aravind set up. That call is happening on 2/11 at 9am ET
Bruce has a question about whether our ACS folks have the ability to support Appian. I told him I'd ask Aravind and co to make sure they are prepared to answer to that.

There was a request from the Solstice team for "service keys". I didn't understand the request, so I pulled in Chris Andrist for help

The answer was "The customer needs to initiate the Direct Connect and give use the details and we will connect it. The reason why is that there is a monthly cost just to have the direct connect line. The customer needs to pay that fee. We will only pay for transit."

Logan Baynes from the FFB security team joined the call. They are tightening controls and want to restrict access to their stage environment. They want to make people go through thier WAF.

I told Logan that I would do some internal research and try to get back with him on some sort of next steps.

Two manual CABs to do on today's call. Ethan had rewrite rules and vanity urls to update. We also had a standard deployment.

Customer is still working on Cloud Manager. I have a to-do open to follow up with Brumoon about the status next week.
Aravind confirmed that they have addressed Appian in their presentation for next week.
I patched Haworth to 202601 yesterday. Today I created CDE ticket PRB0843120 to have the servers rebooted early monday morning 2/9 to complete the patching
I opened CDE ticket PRB0843123 for Stefan to add S3 SSDs to the stage and prod author

Tickets opened for AMSSEC2_84a: Preview Tier Dispatcher Configuration Enhancement (CHG3081440).

Adi Kumar will be creating a CDE ticket to do mine, Ed's and Cindy's all at once

Customer call on Friday re: service keys for direct connect. The Solstice team has been asking urgently for us to provide service keys for their direct connect. I ran this through Chris A/Caleb/David B and the answer came back "The customer needs to initiate the Direct Connect and give use the details and we will connect it. The reason why is that there is a monthly cost just to have the direct connect line. The customer needs to pay that fee. We will only pay for transit"

Customer doesn't like this answer and has scheduled this call. David Basham and I are joining.

David Heer joined the call. He's a manager in the network engineering for Solstice. I think he is the right person to work on with this but he's talking far over my head. It's good that we have David Basham on this call because it seems like they speak the same language.
David Heer's email address is david.heer@solstice.com

David Basham shared with Elise and myself the he has found that DC for honeywell was set up wrong. We have been paying the port cost because of the way this was set up. This explains why the customer was asking for service keys.

Elham was looped in and the answer was that we need Peter Davis in on this conversation since he was the one who initially set up DC for honeywell in the first place.

Peter will be back in the office on Monday, so we have to wait until then to decide on next steps. Elise told the customer via email and on a call. The customer is very unhappy at this point but unfortunately there is nothing we can do for them today.
